"{\"uid\": \"enca.com-top-stories-blitzboks-claim-first-medal-sa-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Selvyn Davids  Selvyn Davids  PARIS - Team South Africa claimed their first medal at the 2024 Paris Olympics as the Springbok Sevens defeated Australia.  The Blitzboks finished as third-best and walked away with a bronze after their last-gasp win over the Aussies.  South Africa looked well on course to victory in the second half, before Australia launched a late fightback to score two tries.  However, the Blitzboks showed determination when they scored their winning try for a 26-19 victory on the night.  It's the second bronze medal for the South African Men's Sevens side after Rio in 2016.\"}"